# Error Handling — SmartPress Compression API

> Scope: Backend error model for:
> 1) FFmpeg pipeline stabilisation (large videos)
> 2) Unsupported formats and invalid media [page:1]

SmartPress needs **predictable, typed errors** so the Next.js frontend can render clear UX states and logs can be meaningfully analysed (Cloud Logging / Gemini).

---

## 1. Error Model Overview

Every failure response from the FastAPI backend should follow a consistent JSON shape:

```json
{
  "error_code": "UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT",
  "http_status": 415,
  "message": "This video format is not supported yet.",
  "detail": "Optional technical details or truncated ffmpeg stderr.",
  "retryable": false
}
```

### 1.1. Fields

- `error_code`  
  Short, stable identifier used by frontend and observability (e.g. `FILE_TOO_LARGE`, `FFMPEG_TIMEOUT`).

- `http_status`  
  HTTP status actually returned by the API.

- `message`  
  User-facing message safe to show in the UI.

- `detail`  
  Developer-facing context (truncated stderr, internal code, or diagnostics). Can be omitted or hidden from end users.

- `retryable`  
  Indicates whether the client should offer a “Try again” option or not.

---

## 2. Canonical Error Codes & Statuses

### 2.1. Client Errors (4xx)

| error_code              | http_status | Typical Cause                                    | Retryable |
|-------------------------|------------|--------------------------------------------------|-----------|
| `FILE_TOO_LARGE`        | 413        | Upload exceeds configured max size               | false     |
| `EMPTY_UPLOAD`          | 400        | 0 bytes received                                 | false     |
| `UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT`    | 415        | Container or codec not supported by pipeline     | false     |
| `CORRUPT_MEDIA`         | 400        | `ffprobe` / FFmpeg cannot read input reliably    | false     |
| `INVALID_REQUEST`       | 400        | Missing fields, bad query params, etc.           | false     |

### 2.2. Server Errors (5xx)

| error_code              | http_status | Typical Cause                                      | Retryable |
|-------------------------|------------|----------------------------------------------------|-----------|
| `FFMPEG_TIMEOUT`        | 504        | FFmpeg exceeded max allowed processing time        | true      |
| `FFMPEG_FAILURE`        | 500        | Non-zero FFmpeg exit for valid input               | maybe     |
| `STORAGE_ERROR`         | 507 / 500  | Unable to write/read temp or GCS object            | true      |
| `INTERNAL_ERROR`        | 500        | Unhandled exceptions, misconfig, unexpected state  | maybe     |

Gemini can help refine this list and propose additional codes specifically for Google Cloud / Cloud Run scenarios.

